Exercise 06 — Valgrind: Invalid Read
=======================================

A function sums an integer array.
There is an off-by-one error in the loop condition.
The loop reads one element past the end of the allocation.

The program will likely print a sum and exit without crashing.
The extra read pulls a random value from memory beyond the array.

Your goal: use Valgrind to catch the overread.

  Run with Valgrind:
    valgrind --leak-check=full ./target

  Answer these questions:
    - How many bytes past the allocation does the invalid read occur?
    - Which line causes it?
    - What is the correct loop condition?

When you can answer all three AND have found the flag with GDB, submit it: horizon done HRZ{...}
